Oxford University Press launched the third edition of their popular Oxford Primary Dictionary for East Africa.It has been developed to meet the needs of primary school students in Kenya, where the OUP team identified a demand for up to date vocabulary, with culturally appropriate examples tailored to the curriculum vocabulary for years four to eight.The new edition includes over 650 new words, including new English words such as &ldquo;tweet&rdquo; and &ldquo;antivirus&rdquo;, syllabus vocabulary for classes 4-8 in Kenya, such as &ldquo;upbringing&rdquo;, and East African English words like &ldquo;githeri&rdquo; and &ldquo;kitenge&rdquo;.The launch happened at Sarova Stanley on May 18.